Crystalfontz' modification of Freescale's Community Yocto BSP (
=============================================================

To get the BSP you need to have `repo` installed and use it as:

Install the `repo` utility:

$: mkdir ~/bin
$: curl https://dl-ssl.google.com/dl/googlesource/git-repo/repo > ~/bin/repo
$: chmod a+x ~/bin/repo

Download the BSP source:

$: PATH=${PATH}:~/bin
$: mkdir crystalfontz-yocto
$: cd crystalfontz-yocto
$: repo init -u https://github.com/crystalfontz/crystalfontz-yocto-bsp -b dora-cfa
$: repo sync
$: chmod a+x setup-environment
$: MACHINE=cfa100xx source ./setup-environment build

Once this has completed, you will have all you need. To start a build, 
set up your bblayers.conf file like just below this section, and then do:

$: time bitbake demo-image-cfa-full

You can use any directory to host your build.

The source code will be checked out at crystalfontz-yocto/sources.

Your bblayers.conf file should look something like this:
(You will need to edit in build/conf/bblayers.conf)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
LCONF_VERSION = "6"

BBPATH = "${TOPDIR}"
BSPDIR := "${@os.path.abspath(os.path.dirname(d.getVar('FILE', True)) + '/../..')}"

BBFILES ?= ""
BBLAYERS = " \
  ${BSPDIR}/sources/poky/meta \
  ${BSPDIR}/sources/poky/meta-yocto \
  \
  ${BSPDIR}/sources/meta-openembedded/meta-oe \
  ${BSPDIR}/sources/meta-openembedded/meta-efl \
  ${BSPDIR}/sources/meta-openembedded/meta-gnome \
  ${BSPDIR}/sources/meta-openembedded/meta-ruby \
  ${BSPDIR}/sources/meta-openembedded/meta-networking \
  \
  ${BSPDIR}/sources/meta-fsl-arm \
  ${BSPDIR}/sources/meta-fsl-arm-extra \
  ${BSPDIR}/sources/meta-fsl-demos \
  \
  ${BSPDIR}/sources/meta-crystalfontz \
  \
  ${BSPDIR}/sources/meta-mono \
  ${BSPDIR}/sources/meta-java \
  \
  ${BSPDIR}/sources/meta-qt5 \
  \
"

Contributing (to the depended upon repos)
-----------------------------------------

To contribute to this layer you should the send patches for review to the
mailing list.

Mailing list:

    https://lists.yoctoproject.org/listinfo/meta-freescale

Source code:
    
    https://github.com/Freescale/fsl-community-bsp-platform

When creating patches, please use something like:

git format-patch -s --subject-prefix='fsl-community-bsp-platform][PATCH' origin

When sending patches, please use something like:

git send-email --to meta-freescale@yoctoproject.org <generated patch>
